Comment_glosser: According to the contributor, Raji still preserved numerals 1 to 7 of Tibeto-Burman origin, after seven, they borrow numerals from Kumauni, an Indo-Aryan language with phonetic modifications. Higher numbers 100, 200, 1000 and 2000 are mixed with indigenous terms with Indic loans.
There is a very high level of allomorphy in components meaning ‘10’; some prime symbols are used, but they do not cover the extent of the variation
